Compariso of pt "the platinum searcher" and ag:
Pros of pt:
 pt is cross-platform
 pt may be slightly faster
 pt ignores files in .gitignore
Cons of pt:
 pt requires go to be installed
 pt isn't as well documented
 pt doesn't search compressed files (which ag does, though ag doesn't support all compression schemes and archives).
 pt crashes sometimes: https://github.com/monochromegane/the_platinum_searcher/issues/190 (also witth version 2.1.6)


Ubuntu:
sudo apt -y install silversearcher-ag

# From source:
cd ~/bin/src
git clone git@github.com:ggreer/the_silver_searcher.git the_silver_searcher
cd the_silver_searcher
git pull
./build.sh
mkdir -p ~/bin/`uname`-`uname -m`
cd ~/bin/`uname`-`uname -m`
ln -s ../src/the_silver_searcher/ag .

I have my own fork now at https://github.com/mernst/the_silver_searcher

# From a distribution:
cd ~/bin/install
wget https://github.com/ggreer/the_silver_searcher/archive/0.31.0.tar.gz
mv 0.31.0.tar.gz the_silver_searcher-0.31.0.tar.gz
tar xzf the_silver_searcher-0.31.0.tar.gz
cd the_silver_searcher-0.31.0
./build.sh
mkdir -p ~/bin/`uname`-`uname -m`
cd ~/bin/`uname`-`uname -m`
ln -s ../install/the_silver_searcher-0.31.0/ag .


## Don't do this because it defaults to literal searching.
## To uninstall after doing this:  rm -rf ~/.emacs.d/elpa/ag-*
